race.comment: LAYLA (8) was well in the market on debut at Sandown Lakeside and gave a sight on speed, going down narrowly when third. Better for the run and draw to be prominent again. Looks hard to beat. PAFITIS (3) finished off juvenile season in the Sires Produce and was safely held behind Vinrock. Gelded since. Placed 2/2 when fresh and has the ability. Should go close this level.  TROOPER (1) looks close to a win and resumed with a strong run at Geelong when third after sitting on speed. Fitter and can give a sight again.  SAN MARCO KID (16) is a two start maiden fitter for one run back. Resumed over 1000m at this track last start and finished 3.5 lengths away in sixth. Fitter again and should improve sharply.
